payload.description:
Found by code reviewer 2026-05-10 at internal/cli/create.go:51-56. Spec spec-v2.md:573-575 documents act create JSON output as:

  {"ok": true, "id": "act-a1b2c3d4...", "prefix": "act-a1b2", "op_id": "7f3a...", "committed": true, "pushed": false}

Actual CreateResult struct:

  type CreateResult struct {
    ID       string   `json:"id"`
    ShortID  string   `json:"short_id"`
    Title    string   `json:"title"`
    Warnings []string `json:"warnings,omitempty"`
  }

Discrepancies: (a) no ok; (b) prefix vs short_id; (c) missing op_id, committed, pushed; (d) extra title and warnings. Agents parsing the documented shape will fail on first use.
